	function Att = PZ_2_ATT_S(G, Z, P, W)		%	Computes the attenuation for an analog filter significantly 	% 	more accurate than the standard MATLAB routine freqs. 	% 	Replaces the MATLAB routine freqs 	% 	Toolbox for  DIGITAL FILTERS USING MATLA	% 	Author: 		Lars Wanhammar, 2007-02-19	% 	Modified by: 			% 	Copyright:		by authors - not released for commercial use	% 	Version: 		1	% 	Known bugs:		 	% 	Report bugs to:	Wanhammar@gmail.com		H = G*ones(1,length(W));		W = i*W;		for n = 1:length(Z)			H = H.*(W - Z(n));    		end		for n = 1:length(P)			H = H./(W - P(n));    		end		Att = MAG_2_ATT(H);